              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10899933001347153428">My first in-depth look at Merton leaves me looking for more. Brilliantly funny, VERY catholic, deeply wise. As I was preparing to read this book it was describe to me as a modern day Confessions, and I agree about 89% with this statement. He’s not Augustine- obvi- but his vulnerability and depth of personal insight gave me similar insights into my own spiritual journey.</span>

          </span>
